  "instructions_to_main_agent": [
    "You are building an Expo React Native app. Do NOT use HTML tags (div, span, img). Use View, Text, Image, TouchableOpacity, ScrollView, FlatList.",
    "Do NOT use CSS files or className strings. Use StyleSheet.create({}) and style props.",
    "Navigation: Use 'expo-router'. This means file-based routing in the /app folder. Create a _layout.js for the stack/tabs.",
    "Icons: Use the specified icon library (Feather or Ionicons) from @expo/vector-icons.",
    "Safe Area: WRAP your main screens in SafeAreaView (from react-native-safe-area-context) or use proper padding.",
    "Images: Use the 'uri' property in the source prop: <Image source={{ uri: '...' }} style={...} />. Set explicit width/height.",
    "Interactions: Add activeOpacity={0.8} to TouchableOpacity for better feedback.",
    "Design Implementation: Stick to the color palette and typography rules defined above. Use the spacing scale variables.",
    "Data Test IDs: Add 'testID' (React Native prop) to all interactive elements, NOT 'data-testid'. Example: <TouchableOpacity testID='login-button'>."
